<dl id="n12126c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12126c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12126c"> 126(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> no catholics before protestant</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A cette &eacute;poque o&ugrave; le protestantisme n&apos;existait pas, il n&apos;y avait que des chr&eacute;tiens et pas &agrave; proprement parler de catho-<font color="green">[5]</font> liques. Mais les formes de pi&eacute;t&eacute;, la mentalit&eacute; m&ecirc;me de ce christianisme espagnol du quatorzi&egrave;me si&egrave;cle sont celles du catholicisme. <br><font color="green">[At that time protestantism did not exist yet, there were only christians and thus, properly speaking, no catholics. But the forms of piety, the mentality itself of the Spanish Christianity in the fourteenth century are those of Catholicism.]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 5-6n3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
